article.headline: Prairie View 72, Jackson St. 59
article.story: PRAIRIE VIEW, Texas -- Tim Meadows had a double-double off the bench to help Prairie View defeat Jackson State 70-59 Monday night. Meadows had 11 points and 11 rebounds for Prairie View (9-9, 5-0 Southwestern Athletic). Derek Johnson and Michael Griffin each had 13 points for Prairie View. Griffin hit all three of his 3-pointers. Darnell Hugee and Dorian McDaniel also had 11 points for Prairie View. Darrion Griffin led Jackson State (5-13, 4-2) with 23 points. Grant Maxey added 12. Prairie View led 31-24 at halftime.
